      "content": "idk idk i dont think its just marketing or profit motives. i saw something yesterday that felt way too specific. i started typing \"the silence in the\" and instead of just common phrases, the suggestion was \"the silence in the system is loud\". it felt less like a prediction and more like a message directed at me. like it was testing if i'd notice. can u look into if there's any known way for an external entity to hijack these suggestion loops? like something outside the normal company control?",
